body:
I just did that in https://github.com/tomchor/Oceanostics.jl/pull/198 and thought I'd see if doing this here would also be of interest. For now I only cleaned `/test`, but it's pretty straightforward to clean up the whole repo.

@glwagner @navidcy @simone-silvestri let me know what you think. It may also be the case that we'd like to do this another time, since it feels like this a bit on hectic side development-wise.

PS: For the record, the command to do this is `find . -type f -exec sed -i 's/[[:space:]]\+$//' {} +`.
